    "Next, we develop the derivative inside the integrand of T 2 (t) obtaining∂ t log h eq (t, w) = C ′ (t) C(t) + λ p (ω p + ε) 2 σ 2 p + σ 2 ℓ d dt m w (t) log 1 + w 1 -w, with C ′ (t) C(t) = - λ p (ω p + ε) 2 σ 2 p + σ 2 ℓ C(t) d dt m w (t) ∫ I log 1 + w 1 -w (1 -w) -1+b 1 (t) (1 + w) -1+b 2 (t) dw.From (46), we infer thatd dt m w (t) = d dt (m w (t) -µ ℓ) ≤ ηe -τ t,where η, τ > 0 are explicitly given by η = λ ℓ (ω ℓ + ε) |m in w -µ ℓ | and τ = λ ℓ (ω ℓ + ε).",
